    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Note from an editor: the below answer is from 2009 and may have been, as <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/users/155689/flurdy\">@flurdy</a> <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1873995/run-a-single-test-method-with-maven#comment78688722_1874715\">pointed out</a>, true back in the day. Since then, <a href=\"https://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/examples/single-test.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">https://maven.apache.org/surefire/maven-surefire-plugin/examples/single-test.html</a> tells us that only jUnit 4.x and TestNG support &quot;Running a Set of Methods in a Single Test Class&quot;.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>You can run a single test class, but not a single method within a test class.   You use the simple name of the class not the fully-qualified name of the class.   So, if you have a test in &quot;org.sonatype.test.MyTest&quot; and that is the only test you want to run, your command line would look like this:</p>\n<pre><code>mvn test -Dtest=MyTest\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
