    "creation_date" : 1594990477,
    "answer_id" : 62954423,
    "question_id" : 1873995,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I tried several solutions provided in this thread, however they were not working for module which depends on a different one. In that case I had to run <code>mvn</code> from the root-module with additional parameters: <code>-am</code> (<code>--also-make</code>), which tells maven to built modules which your test module depends on and <code>-DfailIfNoTests=false</code>, otherwise &quot;No tests were executed!&quot; error appears.</p>\n<pre><code>mvn test -pl B -Dtest=MyTestClass#myTest -am -DfailIfNoTests=false\n</code></pre>\n<p>pom.xml section in root:</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;modules&gt;\n    &lt;module&gt;A&lt;/module&gt;\n    &lt;module&gt;B&lt;/module&gt;\n&lt;modules&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>B depends on A.</p>\n"
